The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Gold gala on bday

 ANUMITA GHOSH

 Roopa Ganguly at the golden jubilee celebrations of A. Sirkar. Picture by Rashbehari Das 

 What: Launch of the golden jubilee celebrations at A. Sirkar.

 Where: The showroom at 171/1A, Rashbehari Avenue. 

 When: January 25. The celebration offers start from January 30 and will be on till February 4.

 The celebrations: To mark the occasion, the showroom was beautifully done up with photographs of actress Roopa Ganguly adorning the walls. The pictures illustrated the ever-changing face of the Indian woman, reflected through her taste in jewellery, right from the early 1950s to 2000. Roopa herself made an appearance in a pale green sari. I am a regular customer of A. Sirkar and it is a jewellery house you can depend on, said the Antarmahal star. Also present on the occasion was social entrepreneur Mira Kakkar.

 An array of new designs are on offer as part of the celebrations. The wedding collection is an assortment of ornate sitahars, broad neckpieces, pretty bangles and earrings.

 There are a host of discounts and offers awaiting customers on the six days, starting Monday. The winner of a lucky draw will walk away with a prize money of Rs 50,000 at the A. Sirkar annual award ceremony held on February 5.

 Pocket pinch: The wedding sets start at Rs 20,000. 

 Voiceover: We have come a long way and customer satisfaction has always been a priority. In our journey ahead, we are looking at more innovations, great services and active customer participation, smiled Chiradeep Sirkar, proprietor, A. Sirkar.




